ShortName: Sherman–Morrison rank-1 updates
Concepts: A rank-1 change to a matrix ($A + uv^\top$), the Sherman–Morrison identity giving $(A+uv^\top)^{-1}$ from $A^{-1}$ without re-inverting, that it is exact (not an approximation — verified to machine precision), why it is fast ($O(p^2)$ update vs $O(p^3)$ fresh inverse), and the Woodbury / bordering family that grows or shrinks a matrix by one row+column
BuildsOn: [matrices-and-linear-transforms](matrices-and-linear-transforms/lesson.qmd)
UsedBy: —
